{
  "$schema": "https://aka.ms/codetour-schema",
  "title": "2 - Running the application",
  "nextTour": "3 - Tool Calling: Calculator",
  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Assistant0",
      "description": "# Running Assistant0 for the first time\n\nAssistant0 is built in NextJS and already has all the dependencies installed for you to start using it, including the the [Auth0 NextJS SDK](https://auth0.com/docs/quickstart/webapp/nextjs/01-login#install-the-auth0-next-js-sdk) to take care of auth for you.\n\nFor the GenAI portion we are going to use [LangGraph](https://www.langchain.com/langgraph)."
    },
    {
      "title": "Understanding the code",
      "description": "## Understanding the code\n\nThis is the application structure:\n\n- `src/app`: Contains the Next.js application routes, layout, and pages.\n- `src/app/page.tsx`: Home page with chat interface.\n- `src/app/api/chat/route.ts`: API route for handling chat requests. This is where the AI agent is defined.\n- `src/components`: UI components used in the application.\n- `src/lib`: Services and configurations. This is where custom tools will be defined.\n- `src/utils`: Utility functions\n- `.env.local`: File to hold the environment variables"
    },
    {
      "file": "auth0-assistant0/.env.local",
      "description": "## Update `.env.local` - generate an application secret\n\nNow let's generate a secret to encode the values.\n\n1. Select [this link](command:codetour.sendTextToTerminal?[\"openssl rand -hex 32\"]) to run the command `openssl rand -hex 32` in the terminal.\n\n2. Copy the output and update the value of the `AUTH0_SECRET` variable highlighted on the line above.",
      "line": 5,
      "selection": {
        "start": {
          "line": 5,
          "character": 15
        },
        "end": {
          "line": 5,
          "character": 70
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "title": "Update `.env.local` - Set the app base URL",
      "file": "auth0-assistant0/.env.local",
      "description": "## Update `.env.local` - Set the app base URL\n\nIn order to configure the app to work properly in the Codespace you need to set the base URL.\n\n1. [Select this link](command:codetour.sendTextToTerminal?[\"echo https://$CODESPACE_NAME-3000.app.github.dev/\"]) to run the command on the terminal.\n2. Copy the output and update the `APP_BASE_URL` with that value.\n\n-----\n\nAfter the update your APP_BASE_URL should look something like this:\n\n```\nAPP_BASE_URL=\"https://humble-winner-74xv5jxw462r9pv-3000.app.github.dev/\"\n```",
      "line": 6,
      "selection": {
        "start": {
          "line": 6,
          "character": 15
        },
        "end": {
          "line": 6,
          "character": 32
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "title": "WebApp configuration variables",
      "description": "## Auth0 application values\n\n1. Go to the [Auth0 Dashboard](https://manage.auth0.com/#/applications). And create and configure an Auth0 Application with the following properties:\n\n    - Name: `My Oktane App`\n    - Type: `Regular Web`\n\n2. Then select the **Settings** tab on your **My Oktane App** page."
    },
    {
      "title": "Update WebApp in the Dashboard",
      "file": "auth0-assistant0/.env.local",
      "description": "## Auth0 application values - WebApp Quickstart Client\n\nNow scroll down to **Application URIs** and add the APP_BASE_URL to the settings like so:\n\n\n * In the **Allowed Callback URLs**: [Select this link](command:codetour.sendTextToTerminal?[\"echo \\\"https://$CODESPACE_NAME-3000.app.github.dev/auth/callback\\\"\"]) and copy the output\n * In the **Allowed Logout URLs**: [Select this link](command:codetour.sendTextToTerminal?[\"echo \\\"https://$CODESPACE_NAME-3000.app.github.dev/\\\"\"]) and copy the output\n\nRemember to select **Save** at the bottom of the page.",
      "line": 6,
      "selection": {
        "start": {
          "line": 6,
          "character": 15
        },
        "end": {
          "line": 6,
          "character": 100
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "file": "auth0-assistant0/.env.local",
      "description": "## Update `.env.local` - Domain\n\n1. Still on your application's Settings tab, scroll up to the **Basic Information** section.\n1. Copy the **Domain**.\n1. Paste the Domain value to the line highlighted above to set the `AUTH0_DOMAIN` variable. Ensure you **don't** have a `https://` otherwise the connection with Gmail later will fail.",
      "line": 7,
      "selection": {
        "start": {
          "line": 7,
          "character": 15
        },
        "end": {
          "line": 7,
          "character": 27
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "file": "auth0-assistant0/.env.local",
      "description": "## Update `.env.local` - Client ID\n\n1. From your application's Setting tab, copy the **Client ID**.\n1. Paste the Client ID to the line highlighted above to set the `AUTH0_CLIENT_ID` variable.",
      "line": 8,
      "selection": {
        "start": {
          "line": 8,
          "character": 18
        },
        "end": {
          "line": 8,
          "character": 32
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "file": "auth0-assistant0/.env.local",
      "description": "## Update `.env.local` - Client Secret\n\n1. From your application's Setting tab, copy the **Client Secret**.\n1. Paste the Client Secret to the line highlighted above to set the `AUTH0_CLIENT_SECRET` variable.",
      "line": 9,
      "selection": {
        "start": {
          "line": 9,
          "character": 22
        },
        "end": {
          "line": 9,
          "character": 40
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "title": "Running the app",
      "description": "## Running Assistant0 for the first time\n\n1. Select [this link](command:workbench.action.debug.start) to run the application. \n\n1. Select the **Open in Browser** in the dialog that appears in the bottom right corner to visit your app's URL. \n>If you miss the dialog, you can always select the **PORTS** tab below next to **TERMINAL** and then hover over the **FORWARDED ADDRESS** and select the globe icon to open your app's URL.\n\n1. Sign up for the application. Make sure to sing up with Google to leverage the Gmail tool call.\n1. Once logged in, try asking it *\"What can you help me with?\"*\n\n*Tip: on the first try it might take a while for the Assistant to respond to you. Look for the the `POST /api/chat` call in the terminal to know that everything is functioning as expected*",
      "selection": {
        "start": {
          "line": 6,
          "character": 119
        },
        "end": {
          "line": 6,
          "character": 136
        }
      }
    }
  ]
